Supplementary description. Female (
Fig. 1
). Similar to males ( Figs. 2 , 9 ), but differs in the following characters: eyes less protruding, antennae (
Fig. 10
) wider and shorter, antennomeres V −X without grooves; pronotum wider, disc slightly convex; legs with all tarsal claws simple; abdominal sternite VIII (
Fig. 29
) with a middle and two lateral emarginations at posterior margin, the middle emargination rounded and distinctly shallower than lateral ones, the portion of posterior margin between middle and lateral emarginations rounded at apex respectively.
